$ Python: __build_class__
@ __build_class__

The built-in function `__build_class__` is called when a → development/languages/Python/class is built with the
→ development/languages/Python/statements/class[`class` statement].

This function can be reassigned to another → development/languages/Python/functions which allows to hook into the creation process of classes:
gh|about-python|/builtin-functions/__build_class__/hook.py||

